  "text": "The differences between the sequences of TLCYnV and TYLCCNV strongly implicate C4 as the mediator of the biological differences between the two viruses, although it is not possible, based on the studies presented here, to rule out the possibility that other sequences also play a part. The pathogenicities of the two viruses are different. For TYLCCNV, the betasatellite TYLCCNB extends the host range of the virus to include N. benthamiana and tomato [CITATION_1] . The ability of betasatellites to extend the host ranges of monopartite begomoviruses and even to allow the DNA A components of bipartite begomoviruses to infect plant species (in the absence of DNA B) that are not part of their usual host range is well documented and is attributed to the bC1 product of betasatellites (Saunders et al., 2002; [CITATION_2] Saeed, 2010a, b) . This indicates that TYLCCNV is lacking some essential function required to infect tomato and N. benthamiana which can be complemented by the bC1 of TYLCCNB.",
