      "span_text": "The ability of betasatellites to extend the host ranges of monopartite begomoviruses and even to allow the DNA A components of bipartite begomoviruses to infect plant species (in the absence of DNA B) that are not part of their usual host range is well documented and is attributed to the bC1 product of betasatellites (Saunders et al., 2002;"
